<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title> D3 Baseball </title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link href="css/main.css" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="description">
        <div class="container">
            <h1> 2014 MLB Hits Visualization </h1>
            <p> A visualization of baseball hits throughout the 2014 MLB Season. 
            Hits are displayed as "Hits", "Outs" and "Errors".
            Hits maybe be navigated via hitter and pitcher combinations. For example
            putting "Jose Bautista" in the hitter's box (pun intended), will display all
            hits from "Jose Bautista".</p>
            <p>The current dataset is up to date of as early May. </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="options">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="player-options">
                Pitcher: <input name="pitcher"></input>
                Hitter: <input name="hitter"></input>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="viz">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="info"></div>
            <svg width="600" height="600"></svg>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
        <div class="container">
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Load the scripts -->
    <script src="http://d3js.org/d3.v3.min.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
    <script src="//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.0/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="js/baseball.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
